  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A key requirement (REQ-VAL-01) mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI acceptance. The supporting validation result, however, was generated by a high-fidelity numerical simulation campaign that the assessment narrative argues is 'functionally equivalent to bench-top experimental data given the mesh-resolved shear stress fields and validated constitutive model.' The structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', not 'experimental-validation', breaking the formal inference link even though the narrative characterises the two approaches as complementary.",
